&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ROLE OVERVIEW&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Metals Analyst | Vienna, Austria&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Metals Analyst to research fundamental supply and demand drivers in base and precious metals markets. The ideal candidate will be a junior to mid-level professional with previous experience in metals. Experience working with commodity markets is a plus but not a requirement. Prior exposure to coding and data analysis is a plus.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct in-depth fundamental analysis of metals markets (e.g., copper, aluminum, gold, etc.), including global supply/demand dynamics, mining/production trends, inventories, and trade flows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain detailed supply/demand models, price forecasts, and scenario analyses to generate actionable trade ideas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with traders and other researchers to refine the models.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;REQUIREMENTS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Graduate degree in metallurgy, materials sciences and engineering, production engineering or a related field from a top university.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of commodity markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent quantitative and modeling skills (Excel advanced; Python/R/SQL a plus).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills, a self-starter mentality, and the ability to quickly learn and adapt.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work in a fast-paced environment with strong attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;COMPENSATION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The all-inclusive salary for this position STARTS at EUR 95.000,00. Competitive and performance-based compensation package, depending upon qualifications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

